{
  "workflow": {
    "id": 15428,
    "name": "Create client onboarding packets with GPT-4.1-mini and Gmail drafts",
    "views": 0,
    "recentViews": 0,
    "totalViews": 0,
    "createdAt": "2026-05-01T17:55:06.208Z",
    "description": "How it works\n- Receives client intake data via a POST webhook from any form tool (Typeform, Tally, your website, etc.)\n- Normalises and validates all incoming fields into a clean structured object\n- Sends the intake data to GPT-4.1-mini which generates a full onboarding packet — project brief, success metrics, kickoff checklist, first-week plan, and clarifying questions\n- Parses the AI output and formats it into a Gmail-ready HTML email\n- Saves a pre-written kickoff email as a Gmail draft addressed to your client, ready for your review\n- Returns the complete packet as a JSON response to the webhook caller\n\nSet up steps\n- Connect your OpenAI credential to the OpenAI node (GPT-4.1-mini or higher recommended)\n- Connect your Gmail OAuth2 credential to the Gmail node\n- Activate the workflow and copy the generated webhook URL\n- Point your intake form to the webhook URL using a POST request\n- Map your form fields to: client_name, client_email, company, website, service, goal, target_audience, deadline, budget, notes, sender_name\n- Submit a test entry to confirm the Gmail draft is created correctly",
    "workflow": {
      "id": "Z2eJyq6uEAO24JOc",
      "meta": {
        "instanceId": "c4f5e0a9b5b38ce95d18a39733b2eec2a6f313f4c764907d5c98cdeb2bedff06"
      },
      "name": "Client Onboarding Packet Generator",
      "tags": [],
      "nodes": [
        {
          "id": "d425a090-753a-4de3-b207-f0bb4b56e266",
          "name": "Setup Note",
          "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
          "position": [
            -848,
            -336
          ],
          "parameters": {
            "color": 5,
            "width": 788,
            "height": 1620,
            "content": "## 📋 Client Onboarding Packet Generator\n\nReceives client intake data via webhook, generates a structured AI onboarding packet using GPT-4.1-mini, and saves a ready-to-review kickoff email as a Gmail draft.\n\n---\n\n## ⚙️ How It Works\n\n**1. Webhook - Client Intake**\nListens for a `POST` request from your intake form (Typeform, Tally, your website, etc.) carrying the client's details.\n\n**2. Prepare Client Intake**\nNormalises incoming fields into a clean object. Handles alternate field names gracefully — e.g. `name` → `client_name`, `email` → `client_email`.\n\n**3. OpenAI - Build Onboarding Packet**\nSends the cleaned intake to GPT-4.1-mini and returns a structured JSON packet with:\n- `project_brief` — a short summary paragraph\n- `success_metrics` — 3 measurable outcomes\n- `kickoff_checklist` — 5 actionable steps\n- `missing_information` — clarifying questions to ask\n- `first_week_plan` — Day 1, 2, 3 task breakdown\n- `kickoff_email` — subject line + plain text body\n\n**4. Parse Packet JSON**\nStrips markdown fences from the AI output and parses it into clean JSON. Falls back gracefully if parsing fails — preserves `raw_output` for debugging.\n\n**5. Gmail - Create Kickoff Draft**\nCreates a draft email in your Gmail addressed to the client's email. Ready for your review before sending — nothing is auto-sent.\n\n**6. Respond with Packet**\nReturns the full packet as a JSON response to the webhook caller, including `status`, `company`, and the complete `packet` object.\n\n---\n\n## 🔧 Setup Checklist\n\n- [ ] Add your **OpenAI** credential to the OpenAI node\n- [ ] Connect your **Gmail OAuth2** credential to the Gmail node\n- [ ] Activate the workflow and copy the **webhook URL**\n- [ ] Point your intake form to the webhook URL as a `POST` request\n- [ ] Send a test submission with the fields listed below\n\n---\n\n## 📥 Webhook Input Fields\n\n| Field | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `client_name` | Full name of the client |\n| `client_email` | Client's email address |\n| `company` | Company or brand name |\n| `website` | Client's website URL |\n| `service` | Service or project type |\n| `goal` | Primary goal or objective |\n| `target_audience` | Who they're trying to reach |\n| `deadline` | Project deadline |\n| `budget` | Estimated budget |\n| `notes` | Any extra context |\n| `sender_name` | Your name (signs the email) |\n\n---\n\n## ⚠️ Things to Know\n\n- AI temperature is set to `0.2` for consistent, structured output\n- If OpenAI returns malformed JSON, the raw output is preserved in `raw_output`\n- The Gmail draft is **never auto-sent** — always review before sending\n- You can swap the OpenAI node for Claude or Gemini with minimal changes."
          },
          "typeVersion": 1
        },
        {
          "id": "1518a249-7141-4ebb-ac22-7f2390935fe7",
          "name": "Webhook - Client Intake",
          "type": "n8n-nodes-base.webhook",
          "position": [
            320,
            320
          ],
          "webhookId": "client-onboarding-packet",
          "parameters": {
            "path": "client-onboarding-packet",
            "options": {},
            "httpMethod": "POST",
            "responseMode": "responseNode"
          },
          "typeVersion": 2
        },
        {
          "id": "78292ba6-76de-4a6d-b9dd-2091845ac667",
          "name": "Prepare Client Intake",
          "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
          "position": [
            560,
            320
          ],
          "parameters": {
            "jsCode": "const body = $input.first().json.body || $input.first().json;\n\nconst intake = {\n  client_name: body.client_name || body.name || \"\",\n  client_email: body.client_email || body.email || \"\",\n  company: body.company || \"\",\n  website: body.website || \"\",\n  service: body.service || body.project_type || \"\",\n  goal: body.goal || body.primary_goal || \"\",\n  target_audience: body.target_audience || \"\",\n  deadline: body.deadline || \"\",\n  budget: body.budget || \"\",\n  notes: body.notes || body.context || \"\",\n  sender_name: body.sender_name || \"Your Name\"\n};\n\nreturn [{ json: { intake } }];"
          },
          "typeVersion": 2
        },
        {
          "id": "bb6dd5cc-0863-4d49-99d2-9c20f2a45a67",
          "name": "OpenAI - Build Onboarding Packet",
          "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.openAi",
          "position": [
            752,
            320
          ],
          "parameters": {
            "modelId": {
              "__rl": true,
              "mode": "list",
              "value": "gpt-4.1-mini",
              "cachedResultName": "gpt-4.1-mini"
            },
            "options": {
              "temperature": 0.2
            },
            "messages": {
              "values": [
                {
                  "role": "system",
                  "content": "You create concise client onboarding packets for agencies and freelancers. Return only valid JSON. No markdown."
                },
                {
                  "content": "=Create a client onboarding packet from this intake:\n{{ JSON.stringify($json.intake, null, 2) }}\n\nReturn this JSON shape:\n{\n  \"project_brief\": \"short paragraph\",\n  \"success_metrics\": [\"metric 1\", \"metric 2\", \"metric 3\"],\n  \"kickoff_checklist\": [\"step 1\", \"step 2\", \"step 3\", \"step 4\", \"step 5\"],\n  \"missing_information\": [\"question 1\", \"question 2\"],\n  \"first_week_plan\": [\n    {\"day\": \"Day 1\", \"task\": \"...\"},\n    {\"day\": \"Day 2\", \"task\": \"...\"},\n    {\"day\": \"Day 3\", \"task\": \"...\"}\n  ],\n  \"kickoff_email\": {\n    \"subject\": \"...\",\n    \"body\": \"plain text email with line breaks\"\n  }\n}"
                }
              ]
            }
          },
          "credentials": {
            "openAiApi": {
              "id": "dWZE7Xayo3sogEBG",
              "name": "OpenAi account"
            }
          },
          "typeVersion": 1.4
        },
        {
          "id": "91e581f6-d2ee-4dc4-a556-fdd114fdb475",
          "name": "Parse Packet JSON",
          "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
          "position": [
            1088,
            320
          ],
          "parameters": {
            "jsCode": "const raw = $json.message?.content || $json.text || \"{}\";\nconst cleaned = raw.replace(/^```json\\s*/i, \"\").replace(/^```\\s*/i, \"\").replace(/```$/i, \"\").trim();\nlet packet;\ntry {\n  packet = JSON.parse(cleaned);\n} catch (error) {\n  packet = {\n    parse_warning: error.message,\n    raw_output: raw\n  };\n}\n\nconst intake = $(\"Prepare Client Intake\").first().json.intake;\nconst kickoffEmail = packet.kickoff_email || {};\nconst subject = kickoffEmail.subject || `Kickoff packet for ${intake.company || intake.client_name}`;\nconst message = kickoffEmail.body || raw;\n\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    ...packet,\n    client_email: intake.client_email,\n    company: intake.company,\n    subject,\n    gmail_html: message.replace(/\\n/g, \"<br>\"),\n    publish_note: \"Replace the webhook test body with your own client intake form fields.\"\n  }\n}];"
          },
          "typeVersion": 2
        },
        {
